==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Annealing
<hw>An*neal"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The process used to
render glass, iron, etc., less brittle, performed by allowing them to
cool very gradually from a high heat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The burning of metallic colors into glass,
earthenware, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Annectent</ent>⟦br⟧
